					<p>Our curated list of recent, suggested listening, reading and viewing.</p>

					<dl>
						<dt>
							<svg><use xlink:href="#article" /></svg> 
							<a href="https://www.sovietbusstops.com">Soviet Bus Stops</a>
						</dt>
						<dd>Christopher Herwig's <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09JP2GGTL?binding=hardcover" target="_blank">two books of Soviet Bus Stops</a> are excellent, and now I'm finding there's a documentary?! I sincerely hope I get the opportunity to see this somehow.</dd>

						<dt>
							<svg><use xlink:href="#article" /></svg> 
							<a href="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/2025/01/nick-cave-amalgams-graphts/">Nick Cave’s Nearly 26-Foot Bronze Stands for Resistance Amid Oppression</a>
						</dt>
						<dd>Neat sculptures by Nick Cave. Not <a href="https://www.nickcave.com/" target="_blank">the Nick Cave you're probably thinking of</a>, but rather this <a href="https://www.instagram.com/nickcaveart" target="_blank">other Nick Cave</a> that you probably were not thinking of. I am somewhat perplexed the article never bothers to disambiguate the two, not least of which because I assumed, when I saw the headline, the article was actually about sculptures by the Nick Cave you probably were thinking of.</dd>

						<dt>
							<svg><use xlink:href="#youtube" /></svg> 
							<a href="https://youtu.be/iDr3or33WW0?si=-yKrYLKw9Nv22o4h">In Conversation | with Magnum Photo's Mark Power</a>
						</dt>
						<dd>A lovely video portrait of British "documentary" photographer Mark Power.</dd>

						<dt>
							<svg><use xlink:href="#youtube" /></svg> 
							<a href="https://youtu.be/i-5yvvpM_as?si=naLWDtTUifQClTpX">How the surreal 'Dali Atomicus' was captured | BBC Global</a>
